==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Garage
<hw>Ga`rage"</hw> <pr>(g⟦adot⟧`r⟦aum⟧zh" <it>or</it> g⟦adot⟧`r⟦aum⟧j"
<it>or</it> (<it>Brit.</it>) g⟦adot⟧r"⟦asl⟧j)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>an enclosed structure for housing or
parking motor vehicles, especially automobiles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(A⟦eum⟧ronautics)</fld> <def>A shed for housing an
airship or flying machine; a hangar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A side way or space in a canal to enable vessels to
pass each other; a siding.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>a commercial establishment that repairs or services
automobiles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Garage</ent>⟦br⟧

